gomodel:SYNGO_566  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4e shows localisation of WASF1(WAVE1) in puncta, with a preference towards dendritic protrusions and spines, upon over expression of WASF1 through WAVE1-GFP plasmid.. Experimental description: Primary hippocampal neurons, taken from P1 pups and grown on a glia bed for 10-20 days were used (Goldin et al. 2001). Cultures were transfected at the age of 7-8 days in vitro (DIV) and visualized within the following week (11-14 DIV).\n\n14/11/2017 Pim\n- Species of the neuronal culture not stated in the paper. Species traced back to rat via PMID:11150335 referenced in the M&M section.\n- Overexpressed WAVE1 was of mouse species: \" Mouse brain was used to prepare cDNA from which WAVE1, WAVE3, and Nck1\"\n- Annotation made to the mouse species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_566" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

